video_description: Serving kristy at the end 😏 I personally love Penne Alla Vodka. It’s my favorite pasta dish. It’s a staple in my home and I wanted to share it with you! Let me know what your favorite pasta is, maybe I’ll make it soon!😉 Recipe Below. Penne Alla Vodka Recipe Ingredients  	•	1 lb bag Penne pasta 	•	1 package of Prosciutto 	•	3 Garlic Cloves (or more I love garlic I do 6) 	•	1/2 cup heavy cream 	•	3-4 Tablespoons, Titos Vodka (any brand works I use Tito’s) 	•	1 28oz Can Whole Peeled Tomatoes 	•	1 bunch of fresh Basil 	•	3 Tablespoons Olive Oil 	•	3 Tablespoons Unsalted Butter 	•	Minced Parsley for garnish 	•	Grated Parmesan for garnish 	•	Salt & Pepper Instructions:  First, start a pot of boiling water for your pasta. While that comes to a boil, cube your prosciutto and mince the garlic and parsley. In a food processor, blitz your tomatoes (I like mine kind of chunky so I do a very quick 2-5 second blitz). In a medium-low pan, add your olive oil, prosciutto, and garlic. cook down until the garlic starts to slightly brown. Add basil bunch. Then add vodka, and turn heat down momentarily to avoid flare up then turn the heat back up to medium. This is normally a good time to drop your pasta in and cook according to box instructions. Once the vodka has reduced, add your blitzed tomato. Reduce the liquid until it’s thick enough to run your spoon through the middle and no liquid fills in. Add your salt & pepper to taste. Then add your heavy cream. Stir till combined. Add butter and stir. Add cooked pasta and serve with grated Parmesan and parsley for garnish.

Save + Share For The Future) Sky Biking Anyone? This is hands down for the adventurous at heart ♥️ Only 1000ksh per person It’s located in Tigoni at Burudani Adventure Park about 40mins from Nairobi . The directions are pretty straightforward and they’ve got proper signage by the roadside   One is advised to place a food order upon arrival as it takes a while to be prepared, Though it’s totally worth the wait! They’ve got loads of activities to keep you occupied like zip lining, high ropes obstacles course, normal biking ,giant Jenga and much more  *TIPS* > Go with a group of friends, colleagues as it’s @burudaniadventurepark is great for team building activities   > Dress warmly as Tigoni gets pretty cold  > Place your food orders upon arrival   > Dress in sporty attire or jeans and sport shoes  > Have a can do attitude! As my friends says, You’ve gotta try everything atleast once in a lifetime   You might fall off the bike but the harness is there to hold you up so it’s pretty safe... also it’s part of the adventure so embrace it!  #magicalkenya #visitkenya #fyp #foryoupage #skybikingkenya
